data.title: Kylie Name Meaning
data.meta_description: Kylie opens a door to a world of meaning and history. Learn more about this popular name, its origins, and why it's cherished by so many.
data.text:
Fact: Many athletes bear the name Kylie, such as Kylie Fitts (American football), Kylie Masse (Canadian swimmer), and Kylie Palmer (Australian swimmer)​

Continue Reading…

A Deep Dive

Kylie Overview

Meaning

Boomerang, graceful/beautiful

Gender

Girl

Origin

Australian, Old Gaelic

Etymology

Derived from the Noongar Aboriginal word “kiley,” meaning “boomerang,” and also an Anglicized form of the Irish name “Caoilfhionn,” meaning “slender.”

Pronunciation

/ˈkaɪ.li/

Popularity

Kylie is well-loved in Australia and has gained popularity in the USA. In 2023, Kylie ranked #142 for girls in the USA.

Syllable

1 syllable

Length

5 letters

Numerology

8 (Practical, Ambitious, Materialistic)

Name Styles

Modern, Popular, Cool

Associated Traits

Energetic, cheerful, modern

What Is the Meaning of Kylie?

Kylie means “boomerang” or “graceful” in the Aboriginal Australian language. People with this name are often seen as resourceful, elegant and poised.

What Is the Origin of The Name Kylie?

The name Kylie has dual origins. It is derived from the Aboriginal Australian word “kiley” meaning “boomerang,” and also from the Gaelic name “Kylie,” which means “graceful” or “beautiful.”

Is Kylie a Name for Boys or Girls?

Kylie is usually chosen for girls, known for its fresh and appealing sound. The name’s association with gracefulness and beauty makes it a delightful option for parents.

Kylie in Famous People Names, Pop Culture, and Places

Famous People

In Popular Culture

Places

Kylie Minogue (Singer, born 1968): An Australian pop singer and actress known for hits like "Can't Get You Out of My Head" and her role in the TV series "Neighbours."

Kylie Jenner (Media Personality, born 1997): An American media personality, businesswoman, and social media influencer, known for her role in "Keeping Up with the Kardashians" and her cosmetics brand, Kylie Cosmetics.

Kylie Bunbury (Actress, born 1989): A Canadian-American actress recognized for her roles in "Pitch" and "Big Sky."

Kylie Gillies (TV Host, born 1967): An Australian television presenter and journalist, co-host of the morning show "The Morning Show."

Kylie Rae Harris (Singer, 1989–2019): An American country singer-songwriter whose career was tragically cut short by her untimely death.

Kylie Rogers (Actress, born 2004): An American actress known for her roles in "The Whispers" and "Miracles from Heaven."

Kylie Bisutti (Model, born 1990): An American model who won the Victoria's Secret Model Search competition in 2009.

Kylie Tennant (Author, 1912–1988): An Australian novelist and playwright known for her works that explore social issues.

"Kylie's Adventure" (2017 Children's Book): A delightful story where Kylie explores magical lands and learns valuable life lessons.

Kylie Griffin ("Extreme Ghostbusters," 1997 TV Series): A tech-savvy and brave Ghostbuster who fights supernatural threats with her team.

"Kylie's Song" (2018 Album): A beautiful music album filled with soulful songs reflecting Kylie's emotional journey and personal growth.

Kylie Galen ("Shadow Falls," 2011 Book Series): The protagonist in a popular young adult series, Kylie is a teenager discovering her supernatural abilities at a mysterious camp.

"Kylie's Garden" (2016 Novel): A touching novel where Kylie finds solace and transformation in nurturing a neglected garden.

Kylie ("Kylie and the Lost City," 2019 Film): An adventure film where Kylie embarks on a quest to uncover a long-lost treasure.

Kylie Creek (Queensland, Australia): A picturesque creek in Queensland, ideal for fishing and nature walks.

Kylie Bay (New South Wales, Australia): A beautiful bay in New South Wales, offering serene waters and scenic views.

Kylie Street (Los Angeles, California, USA): A lively street in Los Angeles featuring trendy shops and eateries.

Kylie Park (Auckland, New Zealand): A popular park in Auckland, perfect for family outings and outdoor activities.

Kylie Lake (Ontario, Canada): A tranquil lake in Ontario, known for its clear waters and excellent fishing spots.

Kylie Reserve (Victoria, Australia): A nature reserve in Victoria, offering hiking trails and wildlife spotting opportunities.

Kylie Island (British Columbia, Canada): A small island in British Columbia, known for its natural beauty and peaceful environment.
